body:
**Description**

<!-- a general description goes here -->
When I try to get an offset path from a source path with GetFillPath() and boolean operation union. I get different results if the path is at a different position.

As you can see the paths are the same but the only difference is the first point after the SVG m comand.
**Code**

<!-- a snippet of code that demonstrates the issue -->

var pathBug = SKPath.ParseSvgPathData("m 450.35434,822.38865 c 0.617,-0.3014 0.617,-1.18 -8e-4,-1.4897 l -88.8175,-0.01 v -14.1176 l 88.8175,0.047 c 0.6178,-0.2555 0.6178,-1.13424 8e-4,-1.43545 -8.9949,-1.11499 -17.90118,-2.85449 -26.6546,-5.20599 -16.69,-4.07019 -43.8432,-25.11432 -43.8432,-25.11432 l 104.71302,26.80432 c 0,0 -31.0553,32.1922 -34.21524,20.52164 z");

var pathCorrect = SKPath.ParseSvgPathData("m 602.35434,822.38865 c 0.617,-0.3014 0.617,-1.18 -8e-4,-1.4897 l -88.8175,-0.01 v -14.1176 l 88.8175,0.047 c 0.6178,-0.2555 0.6178,-1.13424 8e-4,-1.43545 -8.9949,-1.11499 -17.90118,-2.85449 -26.6546,-5.20599 -16.69,-4.07019 -43.8432,-25.11432 -43.8432,-25.11432 l 104.71302,26.80432 c 0,0 -31.0553,32.1922 -34.21524,20.52164 z");
	
	
	var p = new SKPaint
            {
                Color = SKColors.Blue,
                StrokeJoin = SKStrokeJoin.Round,
                Style = SKPaintStyle.Stroke,
                IsAntialias = true,
                StrokeCap = SKStrokeCap.Round,
                StrokeWidth = 3.6f
            };
            
    var strokePath = new SKPath();
    p.GetFillPath(pathCorrect, strokePath, 2);
    
    var offsetPath = new SKPath();
    pathCorrect.Op(strokePath, SKPathOp.Union, offsetPath);
    
    var strokePathBug = new SKPath();
    p.GetFillPath(pathBug, strokePathBug, 2);
    
    var offsetPathBug = new SKPath();
    pathBug.Op(strokePathBug, SKPathOp.Union, offsetPathBug);

	p.StrokeWidth = 1;
	
	p.Color = SKColors.Red;
	canvas.DrawPath(pathCorrect, p);
	canvas.DrawPath(pathBug, p);
	
	p.Color = SKColors.Green;
	canvas.DrawPath(offsetPath, p);
	canvas.DrawPath(offsetPathBug, p);
**Actual Behavior**

<!-- a general description of what was the expected behavior or result -->
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/117271075/204579760-ad11fc86-caac-4c4a-bea3-1b07b65568cc.png)

the result on the left should looks like to the one on the right

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue: 2.88.3 <!-- the version of SkiaSharp that has the issue -->
- IDE:  Visual Studio <!-- Visual Studio / Visual Studio for Mac / MonoDevelop / Visual Studio Code -->
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
- Windows Classic: 10, 11  <!-- the version of Windows you are building for, e.g. Windows 7 -->
